The course focuses on traditional colours/paints. Students become familiar with and use traditional paints (flax oil paints, Swedish red, tar and tar-based paints), finishing products (flax and other oils, beeswax, natural varnishes, milk products), with their making and usage. From the perspective of production building materials such as clay, sand, plant masses, dung, etc. are discussed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Provide knowledge and readiness for using materials of little treatment in building process.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course students: - have preliminary knowledge of natural materials to learn more about; - have an overview of major natural building and finishig materials; - have preliminary knowledge for using natural materials, and materials of little treatment in building.
